{
  "stem": "3475.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, but many people, you see, coming back to Poland-- coming back to Warsaw, a lot of people asked me, why don't you go on the Polish side-- on the Aryan side?",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They called it the Aryan side.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, the reason for that was, frankly, is that Polish people could tell who was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know by what magic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I used to speak Polish perfectly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was at the top of my class in, in the Polish, Polish language, essays and everything.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But they could tell who was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And if they saw a Jew, they would point out right away to the Germans-- Jude, Jude, Jude, you know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Sometimes they got something for it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Sometimes-- just-- they just didn't like Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They, they wanted to point the Jews out to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when you did get caught on the Polish side, you usually got shot.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You know, they just took you out and shot you.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So it was a question of risking your life and being shot or going along with the flow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And frankly, I chose to go along with the flow.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I know some people that went on Polish papers-- Polish side.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But one reason also was-- why I couldn't intermingle with the Polish population is because we had no Polish sponsors.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You had to have somebody who would be willing to, to protect you, to save you.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Now my mother, who looked 100% Aryan, you know, not Jewish-- you saw her pictures-- she had many clients-- Polish clients who were well-off Polish people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They lived in estates with a fence and a gate around.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And she went-- when the, the Germans started closing-- you know, tightening up the ghetto, she went begging to them that they should protect us.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
